All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractAlgorithm
    An abstract parent class that implements basic interface for all algorithms.
    AbstractGraph
    A parent class that implements the basic representation of a graph.
    AlgorithmHandler
    Handles an algorithm form and starts algorithm execution.
    BFS
    Implements BFS algorithm.
    DFS
    Implements DFS algorithm.
    Editor
    Implements the graph editor form.
    Graph
    Implements a graph with IO interface.
    KeyBoardPressHandler
    Handles KEY_PRESSED events.
    KeyBoardReleaseHandler
    Handles KEY_RELEASED events.
    Main
    The starting point of the whole program.
    MouseClickHandler
    Handles MOUSE_CLICKED events.
    MouseDragHandler
    Handles MOUSE_CLICKED events.
    NewGraphHandler
    Handles New being selected (File menu).
    Node
    A helper class that stores information about vertex parent during BFS and DFS.
    OpenFileHandler
    Handles Open being selected (File menu).
    Path
    A helper class that stores information about path, found during BFS or DFS.
    PointD
    A helper class that stores information about point coordinates.
    RunButtonHandler
    Starts algorithm execution.
    SaveFileHandler
    Handles Save being selected (File menu).
    StopAlgorithmHandler
    Handles Stop/Clear status (Algorithms menu).
